  m_text: "These preserved barrels are located at the bow of the ship. In the lowest
    hold of a ship of the line, this is where water barrels were usually placed.
    At the stern were the food barrels. Water was brought in from shore in barrels.
    Obtaining water for the ship\u2019s nearly 600 crew members was hard work."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
