  m_text: In 1997, a ballast block made of iron was lifted from the wreck. The purpose
    of the ballast blocks was to stabilize the ship. The number of blocks varied
    depending on the amount of other equipment and cargo on the ship. During conservation,
    the letters A.F. were found on the lifted block, which refer to the Archipelago
    Fleet.
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
