      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "The sides of the ship were made of oak. Oak was sourced from, among other
    places, the area of German Pomerania. The Navy had its own suppliers for shipbuilding
    wood. The ship\u2019s arches were placed side by side to withstand both the weight
    of the heavy cannons and the fire of enemy cannons. Dark traces of burning can
    be seen at the ends of the arches from a fire started by Russians in 1788."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 2180264, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
