  m_text: 'The arms of the anchor are slightly curved, which was typical of 18th-century
    Scandinavian and Dutch anchors. English anchors of the period had straight arms.
    The wooden shaft of the anchor has been destroyed. A oceanliner could have carried
    up to a dozen different anchors; this anchor represents the largest anchors on
    the ship. '
